8 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Form of petition. (1) A local government petition must be substantially in
9 the form provided by [sections 4 through 10]. Clerical or technical errors that do not interfere with the ability to
10 judge the sufficiency of signatures on the petition do not render a petition void.
11 (2) (a) Petition sheets may not exceed 8 1/2 x 14 inches in size. Separate sheets of a petition may
12 be fastened in sections of not more than 25 sheets.
13 (b) Near the top of each sheet containing signature lines must be printed the number of the
14 ordinance referred or the petition title. If signature lines are printed on both the front and back of a petition
15 sheet, the information required above must appear on both the front and back of the sheet.
16 (c) The complete text of the issue proposed or referred must be attached to or contained within
17 each signature sheet if sheets are circulated separately. The text of the issue must be in the format prescribed
18 by the governing body pursuant to 7-5-103(1) and, unless otherwise provided by the governing body of the local
19 government, use the style and language and form guide of the most recent edition of the bill drafting manual
20 furnished by the legislative services division. If sheets are circulated in sections, the complete text of the issue
21 must be attached to each section.
22 (3) An internet posting of petition language must include a statement that the petition language
23 and format may not be modified. An internet posting must include an affidavit in substantially the same form as
24 provided in [section 6].
25 (4) Unless otherwise provided by law, the following is substantially the form for a local government
26 petition calling for approval or rejection of an ordinance:
27 PETITION TO PLACE [ORDINANCE NO.____ OR PROPOSED ORDINANCE NO. 20_-_ ____ ]
28 ON THE ELECTION BALLOT
